during the twentieth century the city experienced tremendous growth  then rapid population decline the citys population increased more than sixfold during the first half of the twentieth century fed largely by an influx of eastern european  lebanese  and  southern  migrants to work in the burgeoning automobile industry  however since 1950 the city saw a major shift in its population to the suburbs the city population dropped from its peak in 1950 with a population of 1849568 to 886675 in 2005 this is in part attributed to the construction of an extensive freeway system during the 1950s and  white flight  from the 1960s onward on account of concerns over crime and  courtordered busing
